==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|sc=polytonic|σάββατον|tr=sábbaton||Sabbath|lang=grc}}, from {{etyl|he|en}} {{term|sc=Hebr|שבת|tr=shabát||Sabbath|lang=he}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈsæbəθ/|lang=en}}

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}

# The {{l|en|Biblical}} seventh {{l|en|day}} of the {{l|en|week}}, observed as a day of rest in {{l|en|Judaism}}, {{l|en|Advent|Seventh-day Adventism}}, or {{l|en|Baptism|Seventh Day Baptism}}, starting at {{l|en|sundown}} on {{l|en|Friday}} till sundown on {{l|en|Saturday}}.
# {{l|en|Sunday}}, observed throughout the majority of {{l|en|Christianity}} as a day of rest.
# {{l|en|Friday}}, observed in {{l|en|Islam}} as a day of rest.
# A meeting of {{l|en|witch|witches}} at {{l|en|midnight}}. (Also: witches' sabbath ''or'' black sabbath).

